name: Warung Be Segara
address: Jl. Mertasari No.95, Sidakarya, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80224, Indonesia
review 1: We ordered ikan goreng, ikan nyat-nyat, and fish head soup. All was pretty good, though not the best. A good option if you are around Sidakarya.
review 2: Fish head soup, Fried fish, and steamed rice.. You got those for 38k idr (they only listed it in the menu for now) ,.. The restaurant is spacious, clean, and there's swing in it's playground..
review 3: Great place for a good priced meal. (Indonesian) huge areas for groups to gather with plenty of parking.
review 4:
Really good food with great price, would definitely pick this over mak beng.

Try ordering the segara fish package.  The fish soup (ikan nyat-nyat, ikan goreng) is to die for.

Balinese ice coffee, very refreshing in the midday.

Spacious and comfy place for families, live music on satnite, and they have a playground for kids to run around on.

Truly a recommended place to go!!!
Kudos to the chef and barista keeping the food and drink quality.  Will surely be my goto place when in Bali.
review 5: Cheap and delicious food and drink. Fish soup and fried fish were fresh. You will hear Sundanese traditional music while eating in this place.

review 3: The meet ball are so good and also for The ribs are nice and not hard and are very easy to eat and don't need to use your hands.  and you should also try fried Tofu is very tasty and crispy.  for me the ribs meatballs here don't disappoint.  just try it definitely addictive. review 4:
This is a warung bakso which definitely to be a bakso dish to die for and  also one of the best local bakso in Bali that taste Super nom-nom.
What excited me is the Tahu Walik goreng (crispy Fried tofu upside-down) they are often sold out at the evening time as it most wanted item. So if you want to eat it them over the bakso sup, please come during lunch time.

review 1: Fresh bakpao and now it has so many choices of taste and sizes. The taste remains consistent as the first time i bought it ( 14 years ago). Highly Recommended
review 2: Thus place only serves take-away orders. We bought several buns of different tastes; they were tasty. The size of each bun was big enough at a price start from IDR 8k/pc.

name: Churros Coffee & Pastry
address: Jl. Pendidikan No.34, Sidakarya, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80224, Indonesia
review 1: Ayu and her sister looked after us last night. Piping hot crunchy Churros, excellent service and very cheap. Highly recommended. We paid 31k for two lots of six Churros.
review 2:
After seeing a place that was called Churros and it only being a 45 min walk from our hotel we set off! That was a mistake in 30 degree heat. But once we got there Ayu and family greated us warmly. We ordered two coffees and a portion of churros which came to around 47000 IDR. The coffee was some of the best we had all trip. The churros were delicious. They werent exactly the churros we are used to as they were less doughy but great all the same with the caramel sauce.
We asked if they could call us a taxi after our trek which they did so happily. We even met there dog üòÄ. This is a great place to stop if you are going past on your moped or bike!
review 3:
Was craving for churros, luckily this place is quite near from homeü§©

Their churros tasted reaaaally gewd with very reasonable price, though I waited for like 15mins or so, nvm it was worth it.
The place is quite small but nice. The staff at the cashier is very friendly & helpful, even offered me her wifi hotspot bcs I got connection problems when I was about to pay.

Would love to comeback to try their other menus!
review 4: Cute little cafe specialising in churros. One portion of 6 pc costs 25k, over 7 or 8 different sauce options. Highly recommended for a cosy and sweet daybreak around Denpasar.
review 5: This is the best churros in town that i've ever eaten. The texture was crunchy, My churros with cinnamon sugars and chocolate dip is only Rp 15.000, the place was good, quick n friendly service
